ence as an often overlooked but pivotal part of the making as well as the perception of literature and the arts.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2022) 0aArts, Russiany20th century. 0aAvant-garde (Aesthetics)zRussiaxHistoryy20th century. 0aAvant-garde (Aesthetics)zSoviet Union. 0aExperimental poetry, Russiany20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aGesture in art. 0aGesture in literature. 0aHand in art. 0aHand in literature. 0aLiterature, ExperimentalzRussiay20th centuryxHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature, ExperimentalzSoviet UnionxHistory and criticism. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Russian & Former Soviet Union.2bisacsh  aChekhov.  aFreud.  aHeidegger.  aKharms.  aMandelstam.  aNabokov.  aRussian Avant-garde.  aTolstoy.  aVertov.  aart.  acultural history.  ahands.  ahaptics.  aiconography.  aliterary theory.  ametaphor.  apoetics.  apropaganda.  arhetorics.  asymbolism.  atouch.  avisual media.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAcademic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311074321008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2z978311074335708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021 Englishz978311075412408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2021z9783110753899oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978164469708540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781644697085423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781644697085/original  a978-3-11-074321-0  Academic Studies Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-074335-7  DG Plus PP Package 2021 Part 2b2021  a978-